This script allows you to rename the network adapters on Windows 11 and 10.
Warning: This tool is offered as-is without any guarantee. Warning: This tool is offered as-is without any guarantee.


How to Use:

Save this script on your computer as Rename-NetworkAdapter.ps1.

Make sure that your computer can run PowerShell scripts.
You can use this guide to complete the process: https://pureinfotech.com/change-execution-policy-run-scripts-powershell/#change_execution_policy_not_signed

Run PowerShell as Administrator.
Execute the script from the path you stored the file with this command: .\Rename-NetworkAdapter.ps1
Follow the on-screen directions to change the name of your network adapters.
